1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,008
Today's video theme: A Day in the Life of a Student. Let's study hard!

2
00:00:10,008 --> 00:00:13,008
Scene 1: Morning Rush – Cramming for a Test

3
00:00:13,008 --> 00:00:16,074
Good morning!

4
00:00:16,097 --> 00:00:19,564
Oh, good morning!

5
00:00:19,587 --> 00:00:22,853
What time is it now?

6
00:00:22,876 --> 00:00:26,310
It's 7:30.

7
00:00:26,333 --> 00:00:28,799
Oh no!

8
00:00:28,822 --> 00:00:33,181
We have a test first period today.

9
00:00:33,205 --> 00:00:37,195
Wait, really?

10
00:00:37,219 --> 00:00:40,209
Hurry up!

11
00:00:40,232 --> 00:00:45,750
Got it. No time to make breakfast.

12
00:00:45,774 --> 00:00:50,367
There's bread on the table.

13
00:00:50,390 --> 00:00:52,823
Want some?

14
00:00:52,846 --> 00:00:55,632
Thanks!

15
00:00:55,656 --> 00:00:58,369
Let's dig in.

16
00:00:58,392 --> 00:01:01,726
Want some coffee too?

17
00:01:01,749 --> 00:01:04,825
I'll brew some for you.

18
00:01:04,849 --> 00:01:11,982
No, no time. Water's fine.

19
00:01:12,005 --> 00:01:14,238
Alright.

20
00:01:14,261 --> 00:01:17,980
Is the test hard?

21
00:01:18,004 --> 00:01:23,037
Yeah, I think it's really tough.

22
00:01:23,060 --> 00:01:28,527
Did you study a lot last night?

23
00:01:28,551 --> 00:01:34,122
Yeah, I was at the library until midnight.

24
00:01:34,146 --> 00:01:37,914
That's impressive!

25
00:01:37,937 --> 00:01:41,404
You'll do great, I'm sure.

26
00:01:41,427 --> 00:01:44,160
Thanks!

27
00:01:44,183 --> 00:01:46,816
I'll do my best!

28
00:01:46,839 --> 00:01:50,950
All set?

29
00:01:50,974 --> 00:01:56,007
Yep, everything's in my bag.

30
00:01:56,030 --> 00:02:00,547
Alright, let's head out then.

31
00:02:00,571 --> 00:02:04,004
Let's go!

32
00:02:04,027 --> 00:02:11,132
Check the description and top comment for a link to review today's video! *Note: The site may be removed without notice.

33
00:02:11,132 --> 00:02:14,132
Scene 2: Commuting and the Weather

34
00:02:14,132 --> 00:02:18,276
It's so hot every day, isn't it?

35
00:02:18,299 --> 00:02:21,933
Sure is.

36
00:02:21,956 --> 00:02:26,901
How are you getting to school today?

37
00:02:26,924 --> 00:02:30,991
I'm taking the bus.

38
00:02:31,014 --> 00:02:35,410
I'm biking.

39
00:02:35,433 --> 00:02:41,138
Let's walk to the bus stop together then.

40
00:02:41,162 --> 00:02:44,395
Sounds good.

41
00:02:44,418 --> 00:02:50,485
How long does it take to bike to school?

42
00:02:50,508 --> 00:02:56,208
About 15 minutes.

43
00:02:56,231 --> 00:02:58,701
That's fast!

44
00:02:58,725 --> 00:03:02,825
The bus takes 20 minutes.

45
00:03:02,848 --> 00:03:10,614
But biking's tough on rainy days, so I take the bus.

46
00:03:10,637 --> 00:03:14,510
True.

47
00:03:14,534 --> 00:03:20,034
I want a new bike too.

48
00:03:20,057 --> 00:03:24,894
Want to go bike shopping this weekend?

49
00:03:24,918 --> 00:03:27,551
Sure!

50
00:03:27,574 --> 00:03:31,143
Where's the shop?

51
00:03:31,166 --> 00:03:36,866
There's a big one in front of the station.

52
00:03:36,889 --> 00:03:39,523
Is it expensive?

53
00:03:39,546 --> 00:03:44,412
No, I don’t think it’s too expensive.

54
00:03:44,435 --> 00:03:49,634
Oh, that’s the bus stop over there, isn’t it?

55
00:03:49,658 --> 00:03:56,335
Yes. Well, I’ll go by bike from here.

56
00:03:56,358 --> 00:03:59,149
Alright.

57
00:03:59,172 --> 00:04:02,446
Take care.

58
00:04:02,470 --> 00:04:04,970
Thanks!

59
00:04:04,993 --> 00:04:08,093
See you later.

60
00:04:08,116 --> 00:04:11,116
Scene 3: Greetings and Forgotten Items

61
00:04:11,116 --> 00:04:14,349
Good morning!

62
00:04:14,372 --> 00:04:17,406
Good morning!

63
00:04:17,429 --> 00:04:20,962
You’re early today.

64
00:04:20,985 --> 00:04:26,018
Yeah, I arrived a little early.

65
00:04:26,041 --> 00:04:30,075
Has the teacher arrived yet?

66
00:04:30,098 --> 00:04:34,836
No, they’re not in the classroom yet.

67
00:04:34,859 --> 00:04:37,626
I see.

68
00:04:37,649 --> 00:04:42,682
Oh no, I don’t have my eraser.

69
00:04:42,705 --> 00:04:46,972
Isn’t it in your bag?

70
00:04:46,995 --> 00:04:50,661
Hmm, no, it’s not.

71
00:04:50,684 --> 00:04:54,068
I must’ve left it at home.

72
00:04:54,092 --> 00:04:59,125
Here, you can use my eraser.

73
00:04:59,148 --> 00:05:02,048
Thanks!

74
00:05:02,071 --> 00:05:05,305
That’d be a big help.

75
00:05:05,328 --> 00:05:09,311
What’s the first class today?

76
00:05:09,334 --> 00:05:13,400
Japanese grammar.

77
00:05:13,423 --> 00:05:16,808
Did you do the homework?

78
00:05:16,832 --> 00:05:22,698
Yeah, I finished it all last night.

79
00:05:22,721 --> 00:05:26,093
I haven’t yet.

80
00:05:26,117 --> 00:05:29,617
I’ve only got three questions left.

81
00:05:29,640 --> 00:05:32,873
Was it difficult?

82
00:05:32,896 --> 00:05:37,730
Yeah, it was really tough.

83
00:05:37,753 --> 00:05:40,339
Can you help me with it?

84
00:05:40,363 --> 00:05:43,065
Sure, no problem.

85
00:05:43,088 --> 00:05:45,834
Which questions?

86
00:05:45,857 --> 00:05:51,924
The one at the very bottom of this page.

87
00:05:51,947 --> 00:05:57,780
Ah, you use this word for that one.

88
00:05:57,803 --> 00:06:00,803
Scene 4: Discussing Lunch Plans

89
00:06:00,803 --> 00:06:04,736
It’s already noon.

90
00:06:04,759 --> 00:06:06,659
Yeah, it is.

91
00:06:06,682 --> 00:06:10,673
Should we get lunch?

92
00:06:10,697 --> 00:06:13,534
Sure!

93
00:06:13,557 --> 00:06:18,224
What do you want to eat today?

94
00:06:18,247 --> 00:06:22,998
Should we eat at the cafeteria?

95
00:06:23,022 --> 00:06:26,815
I’d rather eat out today.

96
00:06:26,838 --> 00:06:33,173
How about that restaurant in front of the school?

97
00:06:33,196 --> 00:06:38,096
Is the food good there?

98
00:06:38,119 --> 00:06:40,819
Yeah, it is.

99
00:06:40,842 --> 00:06:44,075
It’s really good.

100
00:06:44,098 --> 00:06:46,965
Is it expensive?

101
00:06:46,988 --> 00:06:55,488
No, the student lunch is only 500 yen, so it’s cheap.

102
00:06:55,511 --> 00:06:58,344
That sounds great.

103
00:06:58,367 --> 00:07:02,139
What do you recommend?

104
00:07:02,163 --> 00:07:07,707
I think the curry rice is the best.

105
00:07:07,731 --> 00:07:12,081
I love curry too.

106
00:07:12,104 --> 00:07:14,771
Let’s go with that then.

107
00:07:14,794 --> 00:07:20,146
There are a lot of people, so let’s hurry.

108
00:07:20,169 --> 00:07:22,719
Sure is.

109
00:07:22,743 --> 00:07:26,244
Should we run?

110
00:07:26,267 --> 00:07:31,300
It’s dangerous, so let’s walk.

111
00:07:31,323 --> 00:07:33,867
Alright.

112
00:07:33,890 --> 00:07:39,003
Oh, I see the shop now.

113
00:07:39,027 --> 00:07:42,293
Are there any seats available?

114
00:07:42,316 --> 00:07:44,686
Yeah, it is.

115
00:07:44,709 --> 00:07:49,099
There’s an open seat by the window.

116
00:07:49,122 --> 00:07:51,901
Great!

117
00:07:51,925 --> 00:07:55,025
Let’s sit down.

118
00:07:55,048 --> 00:07:58,048
Scene 5: Mastering Kanji – How to Read and Understand Its Meaning

119
00:07:58,048 --> 00:08:03,039
Excuse me, do you have a moment?

120
00:08:03,063 --> 00:08:07,363
Sure, what’s up?

121
00:08:07,386 --> 00:08:12,719
I can’t read this kanji in the book.

122
00:08:12,742 --> 00:08:15,621
Which one?

123
00:08:15,644 --> 00:08:18,878
Let me see.

124
00:08:18,901 --> 00:08:23,867
It’s this one in red.

125
00:08:23,890 --> 00:08:30,804
Ah, this reads as *toshokan*.

126
00:08:30,828 --> 00:08:34,863
*Toshokan*, got it.

127
00:08:34,887 --> 00:08:38,246
What does it mean?

128
00:08:38,269 --> 00:08:43,027
It’s a place with lots of books—a library.

129
00:08:43,050 --> 00:08:46,183
Alright.

130
00:08:46,206 --> 00:08:49,506
Thanks!

131
00:08:49,529 --> 00:08:53,763
Don’t you have a dictionary?

132
00:08:53,786 --> 00:08:58,978
No, I didn’t bring it today.

133
00:08:59,002 --> 00:09:03,572
Want to borrow mine?

134
00:09:03,595 --> 00:09:06,662
Are you sure?

135
00:09:06,685 --> 00:09:09,351
Thanks!

136
00:09:09,374 --> 00:09:13,731
Yeah, here you go.

137
00:09:13,755 --> 00:09:17,752
Studying for tomorrow’s test?

138
00:09:17,776 --> 00:09:21,809
Yep, that’s right.

139
00:09:21,832 --> 00:09:25,616
There’s so much to memorize.

140
00:09:25,639 --> 00:09:31,988
Kanji tests are every week, so it’s tough.

141
00:09:32,012 --> 00:09:39,193
Yeah, but I’m getting better little by little.

142
00:09:39,217 --> 00:09:42,567
That’s great to hear!

143
00:09:42,590 --> 00:09:47,770
I’ll return the dictionary later.

144
00:09:47,794 --> 00:09:51,231
No rush.

145
00:09:51,255 --> 00:09:55,122
Whenever works for you.

146
00:09:55,145 --> 00:09:58,145
Scene 6: Chatting About Part-Time Jobs

147
00:09:58,145 --> 00:10:03,645
All today’s classes are done, huh?

148
00:10:03,668 --> 00:10:06,377
Good work today!

149
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:09,767
I’m so tired.

150
00:10:09,790 --> 00:10:12,490
Same here.

151
00:10:12,513 --> 00:10:16,213
What are you up to now?

152
00:10:16,236 --> 00:10:20,303
I’ve got my part-time job today.

153
00:10:20,326 --> 00:10:22,826
I see.

154
00:10:22,848 --> 00:10:27,158
Where do you work?

155
00:10:27,182 --> 00:10:30,816
At a convenience store near the station.

156
00:10:30,839 --> 00:10:34,339
What are your working hours?

157
00:10:34,362 --> 00:10:39,881
From 5 PM to 9 PM.

158
00:10:39,904 --> 00:10:42,737
That sounds tough.

159
00:10:42,760 --> 00:10:47,227
How many days a week do you work?

160
00:10:47,250 --> 00:10:50,750
Three days a week.

161
00:10:50,773 --> 00:10:54,485
Do you earn a lot?

162
00:10:54,509 --> 00:10:58,776
No, not really.

163
00:10:58,799 --> 00:11:02,534
But it’s fun!

164
00:11:02,557 --> 00:11:06,746
Do you speak Japanese with customers?

165
00:11:06,769 --> 00:11:08,836
Yeah, it is.

166
00:11:08,859 --> 00:11:11,725
Every day.

167
00:11:11,748 --> 00:11:15,048
That’s great practice!

168
00:11:15,071 --> 00:11:19,138
I want to get a part-time job too.

169
00:11:19,161 --> 00:11:24,548
Well then, should I ask my store manager?

170
00:11:24,572 --> 00:11:27,038
Really?

171
00:11:27,061 --> 00:11:29,660
Please do.

172
00:11:29,684 --> 00:11:31,917
Yeah, it is.

173
00:11:31,940 --> 00:11:35,486
Well, I should be going now.

174
00:11:35,509 --> 00:11:38,009
Good luck!

175
00:11:38,032 --> 00:11:40,499
See you tomorrow.

176
00:11:40,522 --> 00:11:43,422
See you tomorrow.

177
00:11:43,445 --> 00:11:46,383
Take care on your way home.

178
00:11:46,406 --> 00:11:49,406
Scene 7: Shopping and Preparing Dinner

179
00:11:49,406 --> 00:11:55,397
What should we make for dinner tonight?

180
00:11:55,421 --> 00:12:01,214
I feel like eating meat.

181
00:12:01,237 --> 00:12:07,471
Alright, let's go grocery shopping then.

182
00:12:07,494 --> 00:12:13,285
Should we go to the supermarket in front of the station?

183
00:12:13,308 --> 00:12:20,941
Yes, their vegetables are cheap too.

184
00:12:20,964 --> 00:12:28,031
It's so cold inside the store, isn't it?

185
00:12:28,055 --> 00:12:37,653
Yeah, the air conditioning is really strong.

186
00:12:37,677 --> 00:12:41,667
Where's the meat?

187
00:12:41,691 --> 00:12:50,524
Over there, next to the fish.

188
00:12:50,547 --> 00:12:57,532
Do you prefer pork or beef?

189
00:12:57,555 --> 00:13:05,904
I like both, but let's go with pork today.

190
00:13:05,928 --> 00:13:14,161
Got it. How about this pork?

191
00:13:14,184 --> 00:13:24,417
It's 300 yen. That's cheap, so let's get it.

192
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:29,632
What vegetables should we buy?

193
00:13:29,656 --> 00:13:36,289
Let's get some cabbage and onions.

194
00:13:36,312 --> 00:13:42,579
Oh, and I want eggs too.

195
00:13:42,602 --> 00:13:51,270
We still have eggs in the fridge at home.

196
00:13:51,293 --> 00:13:57,806
Oh, right. Then this should be enough.

197
00:13:57,830 --> 00:14:04,339
Yes, let's head to the checkout.

198
00:14:04,362 --> 00:14:12,396
I'll pay for this.

199
00:14:12,419 --> 00:14:15,419
Scene 8: A Meal Conversation

200
00:14:15,419 --> 00:14:19,393
Dinner's ready!

201
00:14:19,417 --> 00:14:23,983
Wow, it smells amazing!

202
00:14:24,006 --> 00:14:30,513
Today, we have stir-fried pork and vegetables.

203
00:14:30,537 --> 00:14:33,670
That looks delicious.

204
00:14:33,693 --> 00:14:36,165
Let's dig in.

205
00:14:36,188 --> 00:14:38,766
Let's dig in.

206
00:14:38,790 --> 00:14:42,256
How does it taste?

207
00:14:42,279 --> 00:14:46,146
It's really good!

208
00:14:46,169 --> 00:14:49,738
It's a little spicy, though.

209
00:14:49,762 --> 00:14:52,595
Sorry about that.

210
00:14:52,618 --> 00:14:57,285
I love spicy food.

211
00:14:57,308 --> 00:15:00,226
It's okay.

212
00:15:00,249 --> 00:15:04,149
I like spicy food too.

213
00:15:04,172 --> 00:15:07,715
Would you like some tea?

214
00:15:07,739 --> 00:15:11,209
Yes, please.

215
00:15:11,232 --> 00:15:15,466
How was your part-time job today?

216
00:15:15,489 --> 00:15:20,756
It was busy, but fun.

217
00:15:20,780 --> 00:15:23,939
That's great to hear.

218
00:15:23,963 --> 00:15:27,063
Are you tired?

219
00:15:27,086 --> 00:15:32,224
Yes, my feet hurt a little.

220
00:15:32,247 --> 00:15:37,349
Take a bath and rest well.

221
00:15:37,372 --> 00:15:40,839
Yes, I will.

222
00:15:40,862 --> 00:15:46,046
This dish is absolutely delicious, isn't it?

223
00:15:46,069 --> 00:15:49,136
Thanks!

224
00:15:49,159 --> 00:15:52,533
Would you like some more?

225
00:15:52,556 --> 00:15:57,089
Yes, please. Just a little more.

226
00:15:57,112 --> 00:16:02,882
There's plenty, so help yourself to as much as you'd like!

227
00:16:02,906 --> 00:16:08,246
I will! It's so good, I'll finish it all.

228
00:16:08,269 --> 00:16:11,269
Scene 9: Daily Conversations and Hobbies

229
00:16:11,269 --> 00:16:15,369
Mind if I turn on the TV?

230
00:16:15,392 --> 00:16:18,950
Yeah, here you go.

231
00:16:18,974 --> 00:16:23,768
Is there anything interesting on?

232
00:16:23,791 --> 00:16:29,258
My favorite anime is starting now.

233
00:16:29,282 --> 00:16:32,191
What kind of anime is it?

234
00:16:32,214 --> 00:16:37,914
It's about high school students playing sports.

235
00:16:37,937 --> 00:16:42,614
Oh, that sounds interesting!

236
00:16:42,637 --> 00:16:46,137
I'd love to watch it too.

237
00:16:46,160 --> 00:16:50,193
It's really popular, you know.

238
00:16:50,216 --> 00:16:54,283
This song is great!

239
00:16:54,306 --> 00:16:57,373
Who sings it?

240
00:16:57,396 --> 00:17:01,989
It's by a famous band.

241
00:17:02,012 --> 00:17:04,845
Do you listen to them often?

242
00:17:04,868 --> 00:17:11,168
Yeah, I stream it online sometimes.

243
00:17:11,191 --> 00:17:15,334
I listen to it every day.

244
00:17:15,358 --> 00:17:20,425
There are so many anime characters here!

245
00:17:20,448 --> 00:17:27,481
Yeah, I really like that guy with the long hair.

246
00:17:27,504 --> 00:17:30,538
He's so cool!

247
00:17:30,561 --> 00:17:34,194
Is he strong?

248
00:17:34,217 --> 00:17:40,057
Yeah, he's the strongest—and the kindest.

249
00:17:40,080 --> 00:17:43,947
I'm really curious about the story now.

250
00:17:43,970 --> 00:17:50,070
It airs every Friday night.

251
00:17:50,093 --> 00:17:54,526
Then let's watch it together again next week!

252
00:17:54,549 --> 00:17:58,095
Sounds good.

253
00:17:58,118 --> 00:18:02,356
How about watching it while snacking?

254
00:18:02,379 --> 00:18:05,716
I'll bring some.

255
00:18:05,740 --> 00:18:08,740
Scene 10: Discussion About Days Off and Part-Time Work

256
00:18:08,740 --> 00:18:13,730
It's already 11:30 at night.

257
00:18:13,753 --> 00:18:18,427
Yeah, it's about time we went to bed.

258
00:18:18,451 --> 00:18:22,685
What time are you waking up tomorrow?

259
00:18:22,708 --> 00:18:28,275
I don't have work tomorrow, so I'll sleep in.

260
00:18:28,298 --> 00:18:31,238
Sure!

261
00:18:31,261 --> 00:18:35,830
I have a part-time job tomorrow too.

262
00:18:35,854 --> 00:18:37,891
Wait—

263
00:18:37,914 --> 00:18:41,687
You're working on Sunday too?

264
00:18:41,711 --> 00:18:46,211
Yeah, starting at 9 AM.

265
00:18:46,234 --> 00:18:49,615
That sounds tough.

266
00:18:49,639 --> 00:18:53,226
What time do you finish?

267
00:18:53,249 --> 00:18:57,034
I'll be done by 2 PM.

268
00:18:57,058 --> 00:19:02,091
So you'll have time in the afternoon, then?

269
00:19:02,114 --> 00:19:08,181
Yeah. I plan to do some cleaning and laundry.

270
00:19:08,203 --> 00:19:12,637
I'll help you clean your room.

271
00:19:12,660 --> 00:19:15,371
Really?

272
00:19:15,395 --> 00:19:18,153
Thanks!

273
00:19:18,176 --> 00:19:23,743
You always cook for me, after all.

274
00:19:23,766 --> 00:19:26,315
That’d be a big help.

275
00:19:26,338 --> 00:19:31,910
Then let's clean together starting at 3 PM tomorrow.

276
00:19:31,933 --> 00:19:34,666
Alright.

277
00:19:34,689 --> 00:19:39,356
Did you check the weather forecast for tomorrow?

278
00:19:39,379 --> 00:19:45,515
Yeah, they said it's going to be a really nice day.

279
00:19:45,538 --> 00:19:49,679
The laundry will dry quickly, then!

280
